<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Druids vs. Wizards</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Phazer">Phazer</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:32 a.m. 25/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Druids vs. Wizards<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I was trying a few things with a friend earlier. I found that Wizards tend to have more powerful spells, and can indeed kill a druid with very few problems.

<P>We were both Level 21, and we started off at the same time. We battled about 2-3 times. I did lose all of the duels, but I believe the reason is because I was unable to use Stinging Swarm (DOT spell) This is because Verant believes it is illeagal, and makes the other opponent lose experiance. Just thought I would let you know, that a Wizard can and does have an advantage over a Druid offensive spell-wise. Perhaps I structured my attack method wrong, but I was simply unable to win. Although the opponents health was nearing death, without DOT we are useless to Wizards.
<P>Just my opinion, and I COULD be wrong.
<BR>Phazer
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
